Because the discovery service treats "empty policies" as invalid policies, by design. I'm not sure why you instantiated the chaincode with an empty policy, but even if the discovery service would have supported such policies then it would have returned a descriptor that is empty, because the minimal combinations to satisfy an empty policy is actually not to endorse at all, and the discovery service "answers" the SDK with the question "what is the minimal set of peers I need to ask endorsements from?" 

