That's because endorsers got from channel should be contained in the peers list which got by `discovery`, or it will be filtered. 

And there has always been only one endorser peer got from channel or `discovery`. So, unless the two are equal, the endorsement is not satisfied. As a result, it may take several retries to succeed, or an error will be returned when the `channel.policies.discovery.retryOpts.attempts` or `channel.policies.discovery.retryOpts.maxBackoff` is reached. 

